    <h2>Recommended Tools for Static Site Generation (SSG)</h2>
    <p>Here are some of the most popular tools used for Static Site Generation (SSG) that can help you create fast, reliable, and scalable websites:</p>

    <h3>1. <strong>Arx</strong></h3>
    <p>Arx is a user-friendly tool designed for building and deploying static sites to Arweave. It simplifies the process of hosting your site on Arweave's permanent storage network. With Arx, you can easily upload your built website and make it accessible globally without the need for any server-side infrastructure.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong> 
            <ul>
                <li>Easy to use interface</li>
                <li>Automated deployment to Arweave</li>
                <li>Supports static site deployment</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. <strong>Hexo</strong></h3>
    <p>Hexo is a fast, simple, and flexible static site generator built on Node.js. It is highly extensible and has an active community of plugins, making it easy to create feature-rich websites. Hexo is particularly useful if you're looking for a simple tool with strong support for markdown content.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Markdown support for content creation</li>
                <li>Fast build time</li>
                <li>Built-in plugin system</li>
                <li>Extensive theme options</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. <strong>Eleventy (11ty)</strong></h3>
    <p>Eleventy is a simple and powerful static site generator that allows developers to use a wide range of templating engines. Eleventy is extremely flexible, supports different template languages like Nunjucks, Liquid, and more, and allows you to configure the build process to suit your projectâ€™s needs.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Lightweight and fast</li>
                <li>Supports multiple templating languages</li>
                <li>Highly customizable</li>
                <li>Supports data-driven content</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. <strong>Arweave Wallet (Arconnect)</strong></h3>
    <p>Arweave Wallet, or Arconnect, is a browser extension that allows you to manage your Arweave wallet and fund deployments directly from your browser. It is an essential tool for those deploying websites to Arweave, as it enables you to securely interact with the Arweave blockchain.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Securely manage your Arweave wallet</li>
                <li>Fund Arweave transactions for site deployments</li>
                <li>Easy-to-use browser extension</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. <strong>Viewblock</strong></h3>
    <p>Viewblock is an Arweave block explorer that allows you to track transactions on the Arweave network. You can use Viewblock to monitor your deployed content, check its transaction details, and ensure that your website is properly stored on Arweave's decentralized network.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Track Arweave transactions</li>
                <li>Monitor deployed content</li>
                <li>View block details and transaction history</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6. <strong>GitHub</strong></h3>
    <p>GitHub is an essential platform for version control and collaboration. It is widely used by developers to manage source code, track changes, and collaborate on open-source projects. GitHub is also helpful in automating deployment processes through CI/CD pipelines, making it an important tool in the development of static websites.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Version control using Git</li>
                <li>Collaboration with teams</li>
                <li>CI/CD pipeline integration for automated deployment</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
